Determine Network Security Group Rules

Since these things help you to filter traffic, the rules inside help a lot in making sure that traffic is only supposed to flow the way it is. But necessarily there are default rules in Azure, these rules have priority number of 65000. pretty big right? Well here logically 
the bigger the number the lower the priority which means they're goint to be enforced later than lets say a rule at 2k. What you need to know is that these said rules can go from a priority number of 100 to 4096. Plenty of rules to come by. All of which are customizable thanks to chart below:

